content:
Choose the Sharing or Access Model for Lightning Knowledge

The standard Salesforce sharing model contrasts with the default for Knowledge, which uses data categories to control access beyond object permissions. When you use standard sharing, data categories no longer control record access. Your knowledge base continues to use data categories to classify articles.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience

Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and Unlimited Editions with Service Cloud. It's also available for an additional cost in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions.

To use the Salesforce sharing model for Knowledge:

1. From Setup, enter knowledge in the quick find box and select Knowledge Settings.
2. Click Edit.
3. Under Sharing Settings, select Use standard Salesforce sharing.
4. Save your changes.

You can switch from Salesforce sharing back to data category sharing by deselecting Use standard Salesforce sharing in the Knowledge Settings page. We recommend deleting all sharing rules for knowledge articles before switching back. 

Before turning off standard sharing, ensure organization-wide default access is Public Read/Write and wait for any sharing recalculations to finish.
